reviews.author: Enno M
reviews.text:
I stayed at the Carlos V for 3 nights. They told me breakfast was included in my rolm rate, but I was charged 100 pesos for 2 scrambled eggs. So, watch out - if you request anything other than the breads and fruit on the breakfast buffet spread, you will probably be charged extra. No menu is displayed with the prices, so you just have to be surprised when presented with the bill.

The front desk staff is great! Just not much communication between them amd the breakfast staff, nor between breakfast staff and guests, as the waiter told me they lowered the price of the eggs at breakfast, but this information was not confirmed with the front desk staff.

The pool and gym are beautiful - great atmospheres for a nice swim and workout.

I wouldn't order room service again. The margherita pizza was not made with quality ingredients. Sound proofing in the rooms could be better. Each night going back to my room I could hear some exciting activities from other rooms :o The hotel entrance has a general smell of cigarettes, but as soon as you get to the elevators, it's fine.

reviews.author: Clau Castillo
reviews.text: For one or two nights, it'll do the trick. Very basic place with ok prices. Our room was ok-ish, bathroom was clean, without shower curtain. Wi-Fi barely reached our room. The place seemed to be under renovation. Staff is very kind and helpful. They have 2-3 parking places right in front of the building for free (they also offer a parking place in a garage with a fee).

reviews.author: Leonardo
reviews.text: I found pleasant customer service, clean bedrooms and a functional bathroom. Despite the other reviews, we had no problems spending the night there and paid $70,600 ($14,120 each) for a 5-bedroom. However, there is a lot that could be improved in infrastructure and minor fixes. On the other hand, we didn't have to pay for parking and they gave us hot water for mate at no cost. I recommend it as an economical option.

reviews.author: Pablo Bolzani
reviews.text:
Terrible no matter how you look at it.
We couldn't find a place to spend the night because of the soccer final.🇦🇹🏆... and we fell into this dark place.
Lack of maintenance from the first access step to the terrace. No guest service staff. Deterioration in each of its facilities and in the owner worse..... unpleasant.
Cockroaches in the room. Mites. Water that comes out black from the taps and shower. Air conditioning and ceiling fans approx. 1930's....about to die.
Hygiene? Fine, thanks. It is not safe to leave belongings in the room at all. We need to store ice...they didn't have a refrigerator! Thank goodness I'm not encouraged to eat the breakfast they offer....
As a hotel worker it is a shame that they let a place fall so low that it could appreciate greatly if they reinvested 50% of their profit. Sad reality in a very poor province/city. I WOULD NOT RETURN. I DO NOT RECOMMEND IT.

After explaining to her over and over again, I asked for my money, so the girl at the checkout understood what it means to be celiac, which He gave me a glass. The truth congratulated the cashier for her great gesture. The truth congratulated him.👏🏻👏🏻👏🏻
And as for the ones he serves...he has no idea and very bad attention to how they make fun
Bad people should not work if you don't like it, stay at home, work, whoever wants to, the truth is, it leaves a lot to be desired and it shouldn't be the first time you do it.

reviews.author: Agustin Romero
reviews.text: I am pleasantly surprised with this Restaurant that I visited with my wife and friends. The dishes are very abundant and delicious. The atmosphere is calm, the music plays at such a volume that we can hear each other at the table without raising our voices. Everything is very clean, the decoration is modern and sober, the tables are spacious with comfortable chairs. They have a very varied menu with moderate prices but in line with the very good quality of what they serve, as I said before, abundant and delicious! I highlight the attention of the staff in general. The girl, a very nice and kind young woman who attended to all our needs, I recognize dedication and her service always with a smile.  I recommend visiting this restaurant located in the Hilton Garden Inn Hotel. We will surely return another time.

reviews.author: Franco Insaurralde
reviews.text: So far I only went once to try their much promoted 'cokkie ice cream'. The presentation surprised us because it included more details than we expected. But at the moment it only includes a single flavor of ice cream, I imagine it must be because of the recent nature of the product. In my opinion, a little more variety in the flavor of the ice cream would be nice. The attention is very friendly and the atmosphere is pleasant. There is a lot of variety on their menu and the prices are to be taken into account. Access with pets is allowed and that is worth highlighting.

reviews.author: Yamila Silva Segovia
reviews.text:
We had a brief visit to the province of Santiago del Estero and we went to see this beautiful place based on a recommendation and the truth is that we were more than surprised with everything. We went for dinner twice, the price-quality ratio of the dishes is a strong point of the place, added to the excellent service from the staff that comprises it.
It is pet friendly, a great point to highlight.
The atmosphere of the place is very harmonious and delicate.

All this combination makes you have a perfect time!

Additional: they sweeten the lemonade with honey, it is very delicious.

reviews.author: Fernanda Pereyra
reviews.text:
My experience was very pleasant, I ordered a light breakfast. It came with 3 toasts with seed bread (delicious), jam and cream cheese (both very delicious, the traditional flavor of any cheese and jam, what I did love was the presentation in individual pots and with lids. Then the infusion, I chose coffee with milk (very delicious, it was ready, I liked it a lot). The orange juice was squeezed (a plus point). What I didn't like was the fruit salad at all, it had seeds. pieces of orange, some pieces of apple and the rest pure plum.
An extra fact, there are options without TACC.
The service was excellent, the waitress was very attentive and my breakfast took almost no time.
Regarding the atmosphere, it is very pleasant to enjoy a snack/breakfast, it is quiet, air-conditioned and with very calm music.

reviews.author: Vanesa Gabriela Guardo
reviews.text: A modest place, but full of good energy. The people who serve are always very attentive and considerate (especially with older people), with their menu of generous portions and very affordable prices.  It's always a pleasure to return.

reviews.author: Petu Jaimez
reviews.text: Excellent service ♥️very delicious and filling breakfast

reviews.author: scarpattiw
reviews.text: We arrived at the place at 00:40 because it says it closes at 2am, when we arrived we took a seat and the waiter didn't take long to serve us, when he served us he didn't greet us or bring us the menu or anything, we greeted him kindly and asked him what pizzas he had, He mentioned 3 to us and cut off the conversation we asked him for half and half, in a very bad way he asked us what drinks we were going to have and we asked him the variety of drinks, he mentioned 2 of the amount that was in the refrigerator. The truth is that I would have preferred them to tell us that in an hour they closed to receive this type of treatment, the only time the waiter treated us fairly well was when I went to pay and a man was at the cash register. The truth is that it is a waste to provide a good product with such attention.

reviews.author: Belen Jigena
reviews.text: Bad attention from the waiter! We asked at the cashier if we could have lunch and the cashier said yes and gave us the menu! We sat down, we chose and when we ordered the waiter rudely interrupted me and told us pizza or empanadas that it was already late, that they were closing and that he was freeing up and leaving! I understand the issue of schedules more than anyone because I work in the field and many times we are tired and want to leave, but there are more polite ways to address people! Things are complicated for everyone, there is no point in losing customers due to bad-tempered staff!

reviews.author: Pablo Pom
